{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17632889","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17632889"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:45:56+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:45:56+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17446"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17446","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17446"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10136"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70692"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10136","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10136"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17446"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56156"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4948"},{"type":"tags","id":"7709"},{"type":"tags","id":"7717"},{"type":"tags","id":"7734"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23736"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23774"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70692","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70692"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA researcher measures the reaction times of 1000 university students performing a simple cognitive task and finds the data follows a normal distribution with a mean of 250 milliseconds and standard deviation of 30 milliseconds.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the percentage of measurements that fall within one standard deviation of the mean?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["99% of measurements","50% of measurements","68% of measurements","34% of measurements","95% of measurements"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EFor any normal distribution, approximately \u003Cstrong\u003E68% of measurements\u003C/strong\u003E fall within one standard deviation (SD) above and below the mean. With a mean of 250 milliseconds and SD of 30 milliseconds, this means about 68% of reaction times fall between 220-280 milliseconds.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis pattern of 68% (\u00b11 SD), 95% (\u00b12 SD), and 99.7% (\u00b13 SD) is known as the empirical rule or 68-95-99.7 rule for normal distributions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding normal distributions is fundamental in medicine as many biological and clinical measurements follow this pattern. This knowledge helps clinicians interpret laboratory results, evaluate research findings, and understand the variation in physiological measurements. For example, reference ranges for many laboratory tests are often set at \u00b12 SD from the mean, encompassing 95% of the healthy population.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["In a normal distribution, approximately 68% of values fall within one standard deviation of the mean.","The standard deviation is a measure of variability that indicates how far typical values deviate from the mean.","For normally distributed data, about 95% of values fall within two standard deviations and 99.7% within three standard deviations of the mean.","Understanding normal distributions is crucial for interpreting clinical data and research findings in medicine."],"references":["Sullivan LM. Essentials of biostatistics in public health. 3rd ed. Burlington (MA): Jones \u0026 Bartlett Learning; 2018.","Dawson B, Trapp RG. Basic \u0026 clinical biostatistics. 4th ed. New York: McGraw-Hill; 2004."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56156"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17446"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"d